<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10569] Keyspace validation errors are getting lost in system_add_keyspace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10569</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cassandraserver.system_add_keyspace(
    new KsDef(&quot;xxx&quot;, SimpleStrategy.class.getSimpleName(), 
              Lists.&amp;lt;CfDef&amp;gt;newArrayList()));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;used to throw an &lt;tt&gt;InvalidRequestException&lt;/tt&gt; in 2.1. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 3.0 the strategy validation has been removed from &lt;tt&gt;KeyspaceMetadata.validate&lt;/tt&gt; so the strategy errors don&apos;t get picked up until the schema change has been announced. As a result the &lt;tt&gt;ConfigurationError&lt;/tt&gt; is swallowed in &lt;tt&gt;FBUtilities.waitOnFuture&lt;/tt&gt; and thrown on as a &lt;tt&gt;RuntimeException&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This possibly affects &lt;tt&gt;system_update_keyspace&lt;/tt&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
